title: error: "TORCH_EXTENSION_NAME" redefined in test_cpp_extensions
body_html:
🐛 Bug

The latest pull from master commit a7ee632 fails in test_cpp_extensions with

building 'torch_test_cpp_extension.cpp' extension
creating build/temp.linux-ppc64le-3.6
gcc -pthread -Wno-unused-result -Wsign-compare -DNDEBUG -g -fwrapv -O3 -Wall -Wstrict-prototypes -fPIC -I/home/freddie/miniconda/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/lib/include -I/home/freddie/miniconda/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/lib/include/torch/csrc/api/include -I/home/freddie/miniconda/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/lib/include/TH -I/home/freddie/miniconda/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/lib/include/THC -I/home/freddie/miniconda/include/python3.6m -c extension.cpp -o build/temp.linux-ppc64le-3.6/extension.o -g -Werror -DTORCH_API_INCLUDE_EXTENSION_H -DTORCH_EXTENSION_NAME=cpp -DTORCH_API_INCLUDE_EXTENSION_H -DTORCH_EXTENSION_NAME=cuda -std=c++11
cc1plus: warning: command line option ‘-Wstrict-prototypes’ is valid for C/ObjC but not for C++ [enabled by default]
:0:0: error: "TORCH_EXTENSION_NAME" redefined [-Werror]
:0:0: note: this is the location of the previous definition
cc1plus: all warnings being treated as errors
error: command 'gcc' failed with exit status 1
Traceback (most recent call last):
File "run_test.py", line 420, in
main()
File "run_test.py", line 412, in main
raise RuntimeError(message)
RuntimeError: test_cpp_extensions failed!

To Reproduce

clone the latest master and build from source

Expected behavior

should pass all tests

Environment

  • PyTorch Version (e.g., 1.0): latest commit from master a7ee632
  • OS (e.g., Linux): Red Hat 7.4
  • How you installed PyTorch (conda, pip, source): source
  • Build command you used (if compiling from source): .jenkins/pytorch/build.sh
  • Python version: 3.6/3.7
  • CUDA/cuDNN version: cuda 9.2 cuDNN 7
  • GPU models and configuration: P100
  • Any other relevant information:

Additional context
